  "description": [
    "PAGE 6 Eastt Hartford Conn Gazette THURSDAY NOVEMBER IS 1962 Dog Gone Yes They Is Ahuntin By Bert Kand Wild critters that aint got no home git thare vic tuals by stealing it They just dont know no better Down yonder in the South there be wild hogs aroam ing about looking fer grub Out West there be coyotes doing likewise Some other place I fergit which there be timber wolves or big gray wolves like the one what give Little Red Ridin Hood a tough time But here in East Hartford doggone it they is a diffrunt kind o wild animals a swooping around to fill their bellies They be like wolves but hold on thare a spell Them aint no wolves No Suh Them is just plain dawgs They shore plum fool ed me the way they was a plundering them there cans and barrels Did ja ever rise around real early like in the maw ning before the trash was picked up Did ja ever see some of them cans lying sidewise like and all the stuff messed over in the road Well neighbor Yew caint blame them there jeuvenile delinkwents fer that cause they just dont"
